snippet: As the Federal Reserve weighs raising interest rates, it must contend with both good news and bad news from the August numbers.
abstract: Labor Dept report showing weaker-than-expected job growth coupled with lowest unemployment rate since 2008 heightens debate within Federal Reserve over whether to raise interest rates; most Fed officials have indicated support for hike in interest rates, which have been near zero since 2008, but exact timing of increase has been debate among financial experts for some time.

byline.original: By NELSON D. SCHWARTZ and BINYAMIN APPELBAUM

lead_paragraph: As the Federal Reserve weighs raising interest rates, it must contend with both good news and bad news from the August numbers.

headline.main: Jobs Report Gives Ammunition to Both Sides of Fed Rate Debate
headline.print_headline: New Jobs Data Clarifies Little in Fed Debate
